OL,5,Cprojects
OL,7,FIt also follows a 2024 review by
OL,8,Fplanning lawyer Lord Charles Banner,
OL,9,Fwho recommended streamlining the
OL,10,Fjudicial review process so claimants
OL,11,Fhad "fewer bites of the cherry" when
OL,12,Fseeking permission to bring a case.
OL,14,FThe review found that around a third
OL,15,Fof applications for judicial review of
OL,16,Fmajor projects were refused permission
OL,17,Fto proceed entirely, although it was
OL,18,Fnot clear how many had been deemed
OL,19,F"totally without merit".
